  "CLAUDE.md": "# snap-proj — Claude Code context

Claude Code-specific conventions for this project. For cross-tool context see \`AGENTS.md\`.

## Entry point — Polly

This project ships with **Polly**, the NONoise SDLC orchestrator. Start there whenever you
(or the developer) don't know what to do next:

- Type \`/polly\` to launch
- Or say "start polly" / "avvia polly" / "orchestrate this project"
- Or, if \`.nonoise/POLLY_START.md\` exists, Polly auto-triggers on the next session

Polly will ask whether the project is greenfield or brownfield, then engage the right bundled
skill for each SDLC step.

## Installed skills

**SDLC orchestrator** — \`polly\`

**Requirements & discovery** — \`requirements-ingest\`, \`bmad-agent-analyst\`,
\`bmad-advanced-elicitation\`

**Architecture & validation** — \`arch-brainstorm\`, \`arch-decision\`, \`quint-fpf\`,
\`bmad-agent-architect\`

**Sprint & implementation** — \`sprint-manifest\`, \`atr\`

**Brownfield** — \`graphify-setup\`, \`reverse-engineering\`

**Ops & observability** — \`ops-skill-builder\`, \`observability-debug\`

**Integrations** — \`spec-to-workitem\`, \`playwright-cli\`, \`frontend-design\`,
\`bmad-agent-ux-designer\`, \`bmad-agent-tech-writer\`

**Generators** — \`vscode-config-generator\`, \`docs-md-generator\`, \`design-md-generator\`

**Utility** — \`skill-finder\`

**Superpowers (vendored from \`obra/superpowers\`)** — \`superpowers:brainstorming\`,
\`superpowers:writing-plans\`, \`superpowers:executing-plans\`,
\`superpowers:test-driven-development\`, \`superpowers:verification-before-completion\`,
\`superpowers:systematic-debugging\`, \`superpowers:subagent-driven-development\`,
\`superpowers:dispatching-parallel-agents\`, \`superpowers:using-git-worktrees\`,
\`superpowers:finishing-a-development-branch\`, \`superpowers:requesting-code-review\`,
\`superpowers:receiving-code-review\`, \`superpowers:writing-skills\`,
\`superpowers:using-superpowers\`

Bundled skills live at \`.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md\`. Vendored superpowers
live at \`.claude/skills/superpowers/<name>/SKILL.md\`. Read the frontmatter for
the full trigger list. Slash commands for superpowers live in
\`.claude/commands/superpowers/\`.

## Working in this project

- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones.
- Run tests before committing.
- Follow the project's code style.

<!-- >>> polly (managed by polly skill) -->
## polly

If the file \`.nonoise/POLLY_START.md\` exists, your FIRST action this session is to
invoke the \`polly\` skill in full, and then delete \`.nonoise/POLLY_START.md\`. The file
is a one-shot marker — deleting it prevents repeated auto-triggers.

Otherwise, invoke Polly when the user types \`/polly\`, says "start polly" / "avvia polly" /
"run polly" / "orchestrate this project", or when they seem lost ("where do I start?",
"which skill for X?", "what's next?").
<!-- <<< polly -->

<!-- >>> graphify (managed by graphify-setup skill) -->
## graphify

This project has a graphify knowledge graph at \`graphify-out/\`.

Rules:
- Before answering architecture or codebase questions, read \`graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md\` for god nodes and community structure.
- If \`graphify-out/wiki/index.md\` exists, navigate it instead of reading raw files.
- After modifying code files in this session, run \`python3 -c "from graphify.watch import _rebuild_code; from pathlib import Path; _rebuild_code(Path('.'))"\` to keep the graph current.
